parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the Takata airbag module can cause the airbag to deploy unexpectedly, leading to accidents, injuries, or fatalities. Additionally, the malfunctioning airbag can also fail to deploy in the event of an accident, further increasing the risk of injury or death.
symptoms: The airbag warning light on the dashboard is illuminated
the airbag deploys without an impact or warning
the airbag fails to deploy in the event of an accident
the spiral cable in the steering wheel is defective
the airbag module clip/spring comes loose and rattles.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the airbag spiral cable can cause the airbag to malfunction, leading to unexpected deployments or failures to deploy in the event of an accident, which can result in accidents, injuries, or fatalities.
symptoms: The airbag warning light on the dashboard is illuminated
the airbag deploys without an impact or warning
the airbag fails to deploy in the event of an accident
the spiral cable in the steering wheel is defective.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The unintended deployment of the airbag can cause accidents, injuries, or fatalities, especially if it occurs while driving at high speeds or in heavy traffic.
symptoms: The airbag deploys without an impact or warning
the driver's side airbag deploys while driving
the seat belts lock up as though there was an accident.
